00:46:55,620 --> 00:47:00,860
 Father, I just thank you.

1046
00:47:00,860 --> 00:47:04,860
 I thank you, God, that in moments like this,

1047
00:47:04,860 --> 00:47:09,460
 you come close to meet us.

1048
00:47:09,460 --> 00:47:13,580
 People from all walks of life

1049
00:47:13,580 --> 00:47:15,220
 and assortment of backgrounds, God,

1050
00:47:15,220 --> 00:47:18,420
 you come close to meet us here in this moment.

1051
00:47:18,420 --> 00:47:21,060
 And yet to teach us that same truth,

1052
00:47:21,060 --> 00:47:24,540
 which we all need despite our diversity,

1053
00:47:24,540 --> 00:47:30,700
 which is that one came for all,

1054
00:47:30,700 --> 00:47:34,620
 that all might be united as one under his name.

1055
00:47:34,620 --> 00:47:39,100
 Father, I pray that you would move in this moment,

1056
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:40,780
 that your Holy Spirit would come

1057
00:47:40,780 --> 00:47:42,820
 and would sweep amongst us,

1058
00:47:42,820 --> 00:47:45,460
 that you, God, would have your way

1059
00:47:45,460 --> 00:47:47,780
 amongst my friends here in these seats.

1060
00:47:48,780 --> 00:47:50,380
 God, there are some people here tonight

1061
00:47:50,380 --> 00:47:53,260
 that want a fresh touch from you,

1062
00:47:53,260 --> 00:47:54,980
 that want a touch from heaven.

1063
00:47:54,980 --> 00:47:58,140
 I pray, God, that you would reach down

1064
00:47:58,140 --> 00:47:59,820
 and you would meet them where they are,

1065
00:47:59,820 --> 00:48:01,380
 and you, God, would lift them

1066
00:48:01,380 --> 00:48:03,500
 to where you yourself sit tonight.

1067
00:48:03,500 --> 00:48:06,940
 Others, God, they're here,

1068
00:48:06,940 --> 00:48:13,860
 and God, what they need is humbling.

1069
00:48:15,780 --> 00:48:17,980
 I think about the Pharisees in this story,

1070
00:48:17,980 --> 00:48:22,980
 and they have so much line length and page work, God.

1071
00:48:22,980 --> 00:48:26,500
 And yet what we see from their example, God,

1072
00:48:26,500 --> 00:48:30,420
 is that spiritual arrogance leads to spiritual blindness.

1073
00:48:30,420 --> 00:48:32,260
 I pray, God, that for those in the room

1074
00:48:32,260 --> 00:48:34,780
 that may in fact know you, they would say,

1075
00:48:34,780 --> 00:48:38,300
 "Jesus, I'm blinder than I thought.

1076
00:48:38,300 --> 00:48:41,620
 "Would you light up my life, give me new sight,

1077
00:48:41,620 --> 00:48:43,660
 "and lead me in the way everlasting?"

1078
00:48:45,060 --> 00:48:50,060
 For others, tonight, God, is a night of salvation,

1079
00:48:50,060 --> 00:48:52,500
 that they might look to you and say,

1080
00:48:52,500 --> 00:48:56,460
 "Jesus Christ, be the Lord of my life.

1081
00:48:56,460 --> 00:48:58,220
 "I've reached the end of myself.

1082
00:48:58,220 --> 00:49:01,580
 "I am desperate enough to follow.

1083
00:49:01,580 --> 00:49:03,020
 "It's not what do I have to lose,

1084
00:49:03,020 --> 00:49:05,020
 "it's what do I have to gain,

1085
00:49:05,020 --> 00:49:07,620
 "and it's you, my God, that I wish to gain tonight.

1086
00:49:07,620 --> 00:49:11,100
 "Save me from my sin, forgive me of my iniquity,

1087
00:49:11,100 --> 00:49:14,100
 "and lead me home that I might be with you forever."

1088
00:49:15,100 --> 00:49:19,420
 This room is yours, this people, they're yours.

1089
00:49:19,420 --> 00:49:22,820
 Would you sit on the throne of our life, God, we pray.

1090
00:49:22,820 --> 00:49:24,100
 In Christ's name, amen.

1091
00:49:24,100 --> 00:49:27,440
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

